  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      131I-metaiodobenzylguanidine (131I-MIBG) is a norepinephrine analog that concentrates in
      adrenergic tissue and therefore holds promise for cell-specific treatment of neuroblastoma.
      This is a dual institution, Phase II study of 131I-MIBG administered at the previously
      defined maximum practical dose of 18 mCi/kg to children with relapsed or refractory
      neuroblastoma.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
